\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{m+1}$
\end_inset

, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where the first index is the integer,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
the second a term to force a solution that is nonempty to be better than
 an empty solution -- all other things being equal;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
and the remaining terms used to force a solution which uses the same element
